events.name: Los Angeles Lakers at Washington Wizards

headlines.description: — LeBron James had 24 points and 11 assists before resting for the final quarter of the Los Angeles Lakers' 134-96 rout of the Washington Wizards on Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: LeBron helps Lakers build big lead, then Bronny plays whole 4th quarter of 134-96 rout of Wizards

headlines.shortLinkText: New All-Stars Darius Garland and Evan Mobley help NBA-leading Cavaliers beat Hawks 137-115

headlines.description: — Anthony Edwards scored 16 of his 36 points in the third quarter and the Minnesota Timberwolves routed the Utah 138-113 on Thursday for their fifth straight victory and second in two nights.
headlines.shortLinkText: Anthony Edwards scores 36 points in the Timberwolves' 138-113 victory over the Jazz

headlines.description: — Desmond Bane had 24 points and 12 rebounds, Jaren Jackson Jr. made the go-ahead free throws with 8.6 seconds left and scored 21, and the Memphis Grizzlies rallied past the Houston Rockets 120-119 on Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Bane scores 24 points, Jackson hits go-ahead free throws as Grizzlies beat Rockets 120-119

events.name: Orlando Magic at Portland Trail Blazers

headlines.description: — Scoot Henderson had 23 points, seven assists and five rebounds in the Portland Trail Blazers' 119-90 victory over the Orlando Magic on Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Trail Blazers beat the Magic 119-90 for their 6th victory in 7 games
